@@ Description @@
 Add a "Briefing" tab to the MimiWidget that fetches and displays the
 latest morning briefing markdown from /api/admin/mimi?view=briefing.
 The tab only appears when there is content to show.

 All changes are additive — no existing logic is modified.

--- CHANGES REQUIRED ---

1. Add 'briefing' to the activeTab state type and default tabs list
2. Add a fetchBriefing function + briefingContent state
3. Add the Briefing tab button (only shown when briefing exists)
4. Add the briefing tab panel content

--- STEP 1: Update imports ---

Add `FileText` to the lucide-react import list:

  import {
    Bot, ChevronDown, ChevronUp, GitBranch, Loader2, Play,
    AlertTriangle, CheckCircle, RefreshCw, Zap, Clock, FileText,  // ← add FileText
  } from 'lucide-react';


--- STEP 2: Update state declarations in MimiWidget ---

Change the activeTab type from:
  const [activeTab, setActiveTab] = useState<'issues' | 'actions'>('issues');

To:
  const [activeTab, setActiveTab] = useState<'issues' | 'actions' | 'briefing'>('issues');

Add after the activeTab line:
  const [briefingContent, setBriefingContent] = useState<string | null>(null);
  const [briefingFilename, setBriefingFilename] = useState<string | null>(null);


--- STEP 3: Add fetchBriefing callback ---

Add after the fetchState useCallback:

  const fetchBriefing = useCallback(async () => {
    try {
      const res = await fetch(`/api/admin/mimi?secret=${encodeURIComponent(secret)}&view=briefing`);
      if (res.ok) {
        const data = await res.json();
        if (data.briefing) {
          setBriefingContent(data.briefing);
          setBriefingFilename(data.filename ?? null);
        }
      }
    } catch {
      // Silent
    }
  }, [secret]);

  useEffect(() => {
    fetchBriefing();
  }, [fetchBriefing]);


